[ctns_make id='gen_abs_prop_ge_c']

  [ctns_front style='font-size:150%;']
$$|x| \ge c$$
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='font-size:100%;']
$||x| \ge c|$ is equivalent to $|x \le -c \ \ \ \textrm{ or } \ \ \ x \ge c|$
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
The absolute value of x -- greater than or equal to -- a constant -- c.
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
When the absolute value of x -- is greater than or equal to -- a constant -- c,  then the value of x -- is either less than or equal to negative see -- or greater than or equal to positive see.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
